  "id": "019d3876-a223-7a83-a67f-2cbd853f7e02",
  "content": "# Structural Intelligence P2: Python Class Inheritance and Function Calls -- Decision Record (2026-03-29)\n## What: Extended extract_python_relations() with extends and calls extraction.\n## Key Design Decisions:\n1. Two-pass architecture matching P1: Pass 1 for top-level imports + class definitions, Pass 2 recursive walk for calls.\n2. Python uses `call` node kind (not `call_expression`). Separate collect_python_calls() function needed.\n3. Three deny-lists: 45 builtins, 10 dunders (keeping __enter__/__exit__), 11 base classes (including Generic, Protocol).\n4. Subscript base class handling: `class Foo(Handler[Request])` extracts \"Handler\" via child_by_field_name(\"value\") on subscript node.\n5. Decorated class handling: `decorated_definition` unwrapped to inner `class_definition` via definition field.\n6. Keyword arguments in superclass list (metaclass=ABCMeta) skipped via keyword_argument node kind check.\n## Review Findings Worth Remembering:\n- tree-sitter-python superclasses field returns an argument_list node, not a dedicated node type\n- Python generic subscripts (Generic[T]) use `subscript` node kind with `value` and `subscript` fields\n- _private_helper() must NOT be skipped. Only specific dunders in the deny-list are filtered.\n## What Blocked / Surprised:\n- git checkout/restore had file system sync issues; git checkout HEAD -- <file> was needed to reliably restore committed state.",
